&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Information Session:&amp;nbsp;Introduction to CTL Fellowships for Graduate Students (LTF, TOF, TAF)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for ways to extend your pedagogical development? Would you like to be more involved with the Center for Teaching and Learning? Join the CTL&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/about/team/"&gt;Graduate Student Programs and Services team&lt;/a&gt; to learn more about paid fellowship opportunities at the CTL that provide Columbia doctoral students (and in some cases, MFA students at SOA) with sustained professional development experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This information session is one of two that will be offered in Spring 2023 and will focus on the following opportunities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/graduate-instructors/opportunities-for-graduate-students/lead-teaching-fellows/"&gt;Lead Teaching Fellowship&lt;/a&gt; (LTF)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/graduate-instructors/opportunities-for-graduate-students/teaching-observation-fellows/"&gt;Teaching Observation Fellowship&lt;/a&gt; (TOF)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/graduate-instructors/opportunities-for-graduate-students/teaching-assessment-fellows/"&gt;Teaching Assessment Fellowship&lt;/a&gt; (TAF)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this session, CTL staff will review all fellowship opportunities available to graduate students. They will then be joined by current and past fellows in each of the above programs to share the expectations, development opportunities, and timelines for applying to each fellowship. At the end of the session, participants will be invited to ask questions in an interactive Q&amp;amp;A.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note: Information about other opportunities via the CTL, including senior roles in each of the above fellowships, Teaching Consultant positions, and fellowships co-hosted by the CTL and GSAS (e.g., the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.gsas.columbia.edu/content/gsas-fellowships-academic-administration"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Fellowship in Academic Administration&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; and the Office of Academic Diversity &amp;amp; Inclusion Fellowship focused on the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.gsas.columbia.edu/content/pedagogies-race-and-oppression-learning-community"&gt;Pedagogies of Race &amp;amp; Oppression Learning Community&lt;/a&gt;)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;will be discussed in a separate information session on April 21st. Learn more and register for the senior fellowship session &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://events.columbia.edu/cal/event/eventView.do?calPath=%2Fpublic%2Fcals%2FMainCal&amp;amp;guid=CAL-00bbdb71-8581322b-0185-83b6b714-000041b2events@columbia.edu&amp;amp;recurrenceId=" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;here&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
