&lt;p&gt;The CUIMC Office of Faculty Professional Development, Diversity and Inclusion is announcing the launch of a &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;new&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mid-Career Faculty Professional Development&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;Series&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mid-career faculty often find themselves with new career options that may require acquisition of new skills or may be quite different from&amp;nbsp;their work to that point. In addition, development of mentorship relationships and the availability of professional support mechanisms to guide further career development and choices are less available. This series is designed to support the needs of faculty at this career stage.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;This series is designed for &lt;strong&gt;CUIMC faculty who are near or at the Associate Professor/Early Full Professor rank.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
